AWS Services Required for Streamlit-Based RAG Application

AWS Services Used in the RAG Architecture

AWS IAM Identity Center (MFA + SSO)
Provides secure authentication for case workers and manages access to the Streamlit application.

Amazon ECS Fargate (App Hosting)
Runs the Streamlit UI as a serverless container with automatic scaling and no infrastructure management.

Amazon S3 (Document Storage + Feedback Storage)
Stores the original policy documents (.pdf, .docx) and user feedback metadata as JSON.

Amazon OpenSearch Service (Vector Index + Search)
Stores embeddings, performs vector similarity search, and returns top-K chunks.

AWS Lambda (RAG Orchestration Layer)
Handles vector search calls, document chunk routing, metadata updates, and passes the prompt to the LLM.

Amazon Bedrock (Claude LLM API)
Generates the final answer using retrieved chunks and the engineered prompt.

(Optional) Amazon CloudWatch
For application logs, monitoring, performance metrics.
